                    <span>I read this book after so many of my friends insisted it was the their best read this year.  What a disappointment.  The simplistic and shallow characters follow a horribly contrived plot with the seeming goal of manhandling your emotional state into one of forced sympathy for a protagonist you never liked anyway!  The narrator frequently mentions how bad it is to use cliches, but this book is chock full of them.  Don't feel bad about skipping this one.  </span>
                  
              
